American Realty Capital REIT Plans $125M Offer, NYSE Listing



        By Natalie Rodriguez



					Law360, New York (April 20, 2015,  1:40 PM EDT) -- With plans to diversify into real estate debt, American Realty Capital Trust V Inc. announced Monday that it plans to launch a $125 million tender offer in connection with an application to list on the New York Stock Exchange.Real estate investment trust ARCT V, which will change its name to American Finance Trust Inc. once it lists on the stock exchange, has crafted a tender offer plan of $25.50 per share for common stock. The offer is expected to launch in the third quarter if...
				
